^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Marty Bergen recommends the rule of 20 in conjunction with his counting methods as follows. He defines "adjusted HCP" as all of his Starting Point rules ^*Bexcept length^*N (e.g. raw HCP, adjust 3, quality suits, dubious shortness). If you take "adjusted HCP" + length of 2 longest suits and that equals 20, then you have an opening hand. Eddy's hand does not quite make it because his adjusted HCP are 9 -- 10 HCP + 1 quality suits - 2 dubious doubletons. So 9 + 9 = 18. If you changed his hand to Q109x AJ10xx xx Kx then he would have an opening hand using the Bergen methods.|
